  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC Joint Response 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The DRCJR 2020 will aim to provide multi-sectoral assistance and sustainable solution in response to community-identified life-saving needs and protection risks through close collaboration and coordination in the Eastern Zone of DRC.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The World Vision programming focuses on Education, WASH and Protection. It also includes a COVID-19 top up.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall target group of the DRCJR 2020 has not been changed (compared to the DRCJR 2019), as the JR partners continue to focus on the most vulnerable and conflict affected people within the targeted Health Zones. With the collaboration moved to Health Zone level, the JR partners will conduct a joint vulnerability mapping or needs assessment to identify the most vulnerable areas in the HZ and/or agree on a set of target criteria. This will be validated (and revised) by members of the target communities.</narrative>
  </description>
